Due to the variation in the quality of the data, the covariances calculated from all of the RefDB data are not representative, causing the reference correction values to be less accurate. When Cα and Cβ chemical shift data are collected from two separate NMR experiments, two independent samples of chemical shifts are generated. Similar to the batch effects, these two samples are independent and the correlation between the \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
